    "Selecting optimal hyperparameters for graph pooling methods Developing efficient and intelligent hyperparameter optimization strategies to reduce computational effort and improve model performance in performance degradation (Liu et al. 2204).",
    "In addition, graph data may also be subject to malicious attacks, such as adversarial attacks, which are designed to mislead the performance of a graph pooling method by adding, deleting, or modifying nodes and edges in the graph.",
    "Therefore, robust graph pooling methods need to have the ability to detect and defend against these attacks to ensure performance stability.",
    "However, existing graph pooling methods often lack sufficient robustness in the face of malicious attacks and are susceptible to attacks that lead to performance degradation (Tang et al. 2005).",
    "Taking financial risk control as an example, graph pooling methods should have the ability to fight against external attacks to ensure the accuracy of risk identification and processing."
